	<ul>
		<li>V(plain)
			<br>
			Plain/dictionary form of verb e.g 食べる、飲む、行く
		</li>
		<li>V(plain past)
			<br>
			Plain/dictionary past form of verb e.g 食べた、飲んだ、行った
		</li>
		<li>V(masu stem)
			<br>
			The part of the verb just before the 'masu' (食べ)ます、(飲み)ます
		</li>
		<li>V(plain negative) (pl neg)
			<br>
			The part of the verb just before the 'masu' (食べ)ます、(飲み)ます
		</li>
		<li>V(te) - need an extra article on this!!
			<br>
			Hard to explain in English, joining to others、casual command form 食べて, 飲んで
			<br>
			Veyr useful but the u-verbs change depending on their endings (link)
		</li>
		<li>V(vol)
			<br>
			The volitional of the verb. Sometimes 'Let's ...' 食べよう
		</li>
		<li>V(imp)
			<br>
			Imperative form of the verb. Eat! 食べろ！　のも？
		</li>
		<li>V(passive)
			<br>
			Passive form of the verb. It was eaten 食べられる
		</li>
		<li>V(caus)
			<br>
			Causitive form of the verb. I make you eat 食べさせる
		</li>
		<li>V(caus pass)
			<br>
			Causitive-passive form of the verb. I was made to eat 食べさせられる
		</li>
		<li>V(hyp)
			<br>
			Hypothetical form of the verb. If (I/you) eat... 食べれば
		</li>
		<li>V(pot)
			<br>
			Potential form of the verb. I can eat 食べられる
			<br>
			Often shortened in informal speech to 食べれる
		</li>
		<li>V(mashou)
			<br>
			Mashou form of the verb. Let's eat! 食べろ！　のも？
		</li>

	</ul>
